From a26fc2c8bf45dd402c95814a3aebb3656bef35c7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Elias Ellison <elias.ellison@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 21:04:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] [inductor] Fast combine for online-softmax loops
 (amax_sum_sum_6fd07d12d98a, 1.42x->1.01x)

Online-softmax reduction loops (looped scalar-accumulator path and the
persistent two-pass fallback) generated:

  tmp0 = tl.load(..., r0_mask, other=0.0)
  block_max = triton_helpers.max2(tl.where(r0_mask, tmp0, float('-inf')), 1)

Two costs on top of an optimal loop:
1. triton_helpers.max2 is tl.reduce with a custom NaN-propagating combine
   fn; it compiles to substantially slower code than native tl.max
   (~15% on f32[16384, 50257] CE rows on B200).
2. The masked load fills 0.0 then re-masks to -inf inside the loop.

Fix, behind new config triton.online_softmax_fast_combine (default True):
- emit tl.max for the per-block max of online-softmax reductions;
- when the reduction input is a direct masked load whose mask equals the
  reduction mask, rewrite the load to other=float('-inf') and skip the
  in-loop tl.where re-masking (applies to both the looped path and the
  persistent two-pass fallback used by prepare_softmax_online /
  cross_entropy_loss_online).

NaN semantics: exp(NaN) = NaN, so the sum_exp output still poisons any
softmax / log-softmax / cross-entropy computed from (max, sum); verified
NaN rows and all -inf rows match eager. ignore_index CE verified exact
with ignored labels present, absent, and all-ignored (NaN mean).

Benchmarks (B200, oracle --bench, fresh cache):
- amax_sum_sum_6fd07d12d98a DistillGPT2 infer shifted-label ignore-index
  CE mean: 738 -> 531us, 1.42x -> 1.01x AT_FLOOR
- amax_sum_sum_86d05d6810f4 DistillGPT2 train: 739 -> 531us, 1.42x -> 1.01x
- amax_sum_sum_e2f518f0a274 GPT2 causal-LM CE: 149 -> 97us, 1.64x -> 1.08x
- amax_sum_d112f48ea917 Reformer stable softmax: 101 -> 77us, 1.34x -> 1.03x
- amax_sum_sum_0e37ca9164b3 Blenderbot CE: 44 -> 36us, 1.30x -> 1.06x
Regressions: none (amax_sum_f5253e4f250e 1.03x, amax_sum_17ab35828f89
0.91x, sum_sum_b16afac198fb 0.95x, amax_sum_9940b361e5b4 2.54x vs 2.60x
baseline; test_online_softmax.py failures identical before/after).

written with claude code
